<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1932-09-03T13:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1932-09-03T13:00:00-05:00" n="242" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d242">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">893.01 Manchuria/419: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                    State</gloss> to the Ambassador in Japan (<persName corresp="frus1932v03#p_GJC1" type="to">Grew</persName>)</hi></head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1932-09-03T14:00:00-04:00">September 3, 1932—2
                                p.m.</date></dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>156. Your 223, September 2, 5 p.m. In case the Japanese Government
                            communicates to you the text of a so-called treaty between Japan and
                            “Manchoukuo”, please report that fact immediately to the Department and
                            take no other action even of acknowledgment pending receipt of further
                            instructions.</p>
                        <closer><signed><persName corresp="frus1932v03#p_RJG1"><hi rend="smallcaps">Rogers</hi></persName></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>